comments: Green (HOU) brings his right hand forward towards Okoro's (CLE) side and marginal contact occurs as Okoro passes the ball.
VanVleet (HOU) legally contests LeVert's (CLE) jump shot attempt.
Okoro (CLE) is moving forward slightly as VanVleet (HOU) cuts back toward him and marginal body contact occurs prior to VanVleet's gather.
Sengun (HOU) moves forward into LeVert (CLE) and initiates body contact that affects LeVert's SQBR prior to the start of his dribble.
Brooks (HOU) grabs and holds LeVert's (CLE) right arm as LeVert cuts off-ball, which affects his FOM.
VanVleet (HOU) and Allen (CLE) briefly engage and disengage as marginal contact occurs off ball.
Allen (CLE) brings his left hand to Brooks' (HOU) left side and marginal contact occurs as Allen simultaneously deflects the ball with his right hand.
Allen (CLE) and Green (HOU) remain momentarily engaged as the ball falls toward them during the rebound and marginal contact occurs before they disengage.
VanVleet (HOU) and LeVert (CLE) each dive to the floor in pursuit of the loose ball and incidental body contact occurs when they come together at the same spot.
Mitchell (CLE) brushes Sengun's (HOU) arm and marginal contact occurs as Mitchell is raising his arm into a vertical position in the post.
Sengun (HOU) is in the paint for three seconds as he begins to imminently exit the lane.
Mitchell (CLE) is moving forward when marginal contact occurs with Sengun's (HOU) back as the pass into the post is made.
Mitchell (CLE) initiates contact across Sengun's (HOU) right arm after his gather.
Eason (HOU) is moving alongside Mitchell's (CLE) path when marginal body contact occurs at the end of Mitchell's drive.

Strus (CLE) brings his arms forward and simultaneous contact occurs with the ball and Eason's (HOU) left arm, which causes Eason to lose control of the ball before his teammate quickly regains possession.
Strus (CLE) legally contests VanVleet's (HOU) jump shot attempt.
Allen (CLE) grasps and then quickly releases Sengun's (HOU) right arm as Sengun elevates for the ball, which is then cleanly deflected away from Sengun by Mitchell (CLE).
Allen (CLE) and Sengun (HOU) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Mitchell (CLE) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.  Possession is correctly awarded to the Rockets.
Okoro (CLE) is moving forward prior to marginal body contact occurring with Sengun (HOU) as Sengun pivots in the post.
Allen (CLE) legally contests Sengun's (HOU) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
